    "explanation": "【핵심 용어】\n▸ Canary deployment — 신규 버전을 소량(10%)에 먼저 배포하여 risk 최소화\n▸ TargetResponseTime metric — application 응답 시간 증가 감시 metric\n▸ Automated rollback — metric 기반으로 배포 중단 및 자동 rollback 기능\n\n【정답 포인트】\n▸ Canary 배포 전략 → 초기 risk 최소화하면서 문제 조기 감지 enable\n▸ TargetResponseTime metric으로 성능 저하를 직접 모니터링하여 배포 결정\n\n【오답 체크】\n(B) Linear deployment는 점진적 증가로 canary보다 늦은 문제 감지\n(C) All-at-once는 risk 높음, canary 방식이 risk 최소화\n(E) Custom metric은 TargetResponseTime 없을 때만 필요\n\n【시험 포인트】\n▸ 배포 전략 선택 → Canary(초기 risk) vs Linear(점진적) vs All-at-once(즉시)\n▸ 함정: Metric 선택의 중요성, response time 직접 모니터링이 핵심",
    "en_q": "A DevOps team supports an application that runs in an Amazon Elastic Container Service (Amazon ECS) cluster behind an Application Load Balancer (ALB). Currently, the DevOps team uses AWS CodeDeploy to deploy the application by using a blue/green all-at-once strategy. Recently, the DevOps team had to roll back a deployment when a new version of the application dramatically increased response times for requests. The DevOps team needs use to a deployment strategy that will allow the team to monitor a new version of the application before the team shifts all traffic to the new version. If a new version of the application increases response times, the deployment should be rolled back as quickly as possible. Which combination of steps will meet these requirements? (Choose two.)",
